qas.question: When did the First Division clubs resign from the Football League?

answers.text: In 1992, the First Division clubs resigned from the Football League en masse

qas.question: When was the FA Premier League formed as a limited company?

answers.text: on 27 May 1992 the FA Premier League was formed as a limited company working out of an office at the Football Association's then headquarters in Lancaster Gate.

qas.question: How many divisions did the Premier League start out with at this time?

answers.text: the Premier League would operate with a single division

Was there a change in the competition format after the Premier League was formed?

answers.text: There was no change in competition format; the same number of teams competed in the top flight
